@node "history" "History"

@{u}@{b}History@{ub}@{uu}

@{b}V2.6 (October 2014)@{ub}

  - Added support for Z-Com XI-330 and possibly SMC SMC2532W-B v2.
  - Better filtering of duplicate scan results.
  - Removed references to Absolute Value Systems' list of compatible cards.
    Their website appears to be defunct.

@{b}V2.5 (August 2013)@{ub}

  - It is no longer necessary to manually disable WPA2/AES encryption in the
    configuration file for cards that do not support it, as WirelessManager
    is now automatically informed of the card's encryption capabilities.
  - Duplicate scan results are now filtered out.
  - Fixed a memory leak (WirelessManager).
  - Channel 14 should work now (WirelessManager).

@{b}V2.4 (January 2012)@{ub}

  - First free version.

@{b}V2.3 (July 2011)@{ub}

  - Fixed a bug in replay-attack prevention that stopped broadcast and
    multicast frames being received from some access points. This caused
    DHCP and some incoming connections to fail.

@{b}V2.2 (June 2011)@{ub}

  - Connecting to hidden networks is now possible.

@{b}V2.1 (May 2011)@{ub}

  - First WPA/WPA2-capable release.
  - Added WirelessManager program for setting up wireless connections.
  - Network scanning is now supported.
  - Removed obsolete SetPrism2Defaults program.
  - WEP processing is now done in software for cards that can't handle it in
    firmware.
  - Hermes cards in Prism-II PCI-to-PCMCIA bridges are now supported.

@endnode


